routeFacts.name: Cajon Pass
routeFacts.description: Cajon Pass is the US starter route featured in Train Sim World 3, offering players the chance to control powerful American freight trains through one of the most iconic rail passes in the United States. This route is set in Southern California and spans over 85 miles of breathtaking scenery, from the bustling city of San Bernardino to the Mojave Desert. The route is famous for its steep grades, tight curves, and challenging terrain, making it a true test for even the most experienced train drivers.
routeInfo: As you navigate the Cajon Pass, you'll experience the thrill of negotiating steep grades and tight curves as you make your way through the rugged terrain of the Mojave Desert. You'll have the opportunity to operate a variety of different locomotives, including the ES44C4 and the SD40-2, giving you the chance to experience the power and control of some of the most iconic freight trains in America. With realistic weather and day/night cycles, you'll feel like you're actually driving these trains through the heart of Southern California.

The Cajon Pass route also includes a number of historically significant locations, such as the legendary Summit Station and the Cajon Yard, giving players a taste of the rich history of this iconic rail pass. With its challenging terrain and stunning scenery, the Cajon Pass route is a must-play for fans of Train Sim World 3 and for anyone who wants to experience the thrill of driving heavy American freight trains through one of the most iconic rail passes in the United States. So buckle up and get ready for an unforgettable journey through the heart of Southern California!
